1
00:00:06,382 --> 00:00:08,317
Give me your hands.

2
00:00:09,382 --> 00:00:11,317
It's okay.

3
00:00:24,895 --> 00:00:27,393
Is it your marriage ring?

4
00:00:29,034 --> 00:00:34,034
Your wife must be happy
to have an attentive husband.

5
00:00:35,837 --> 00:00:41,737
I read an article that you met her
in America and married there.

6
00:00:42,370 --> 00:00:49,035
And you let her continue her study
for the love of her, right?

7
00:00:52,503 --> 00:00:56,035
Why are you still single?

8
00:00:58,370 --> 00:01:00,035
I know.

9
00:01:02,035 --> 00:01:04,737
Guess I was busy living my life.

10
00:01:06,336 --> 00:01:09,302
Oh, I'm bleeding.

11
00:01:09,303 --> 00:01:12,536
Seems the hen pecked at you.

12
00:01:12,537 --> 00:01:14,035
Let me see?

13
00:01:20,035 --> 00:01:21,435
I'm okay.

14
00:01:21,436 --> 00:01:23,035
Let me see.

15
00:01:27,770 --> 00:01:30,502
Are you daring or reckless?

16
00:01:30,503 --> 00:01:34,436
You didn't know
you were being pecked?

17
00:01:45,035 --> 00:01:46,703
That was close.

18
00:01:49,035 --> 00:01:53,034
Time is the bigger deal
than my scratch.

19
00:01:53,035 --> 00:01:58,035
Hurry, let's go.
I have to try the new menu.

20
00:02:28,103 --> 00:02:33,036
Alright, ma'am.
What shall I tell you first?

21
00:02:34,035 --> 00:02:35,035
Yes.

22
00:02:37,035 --> 00:02:42,035
With this, I can finish
both Minjoon and Lena Jeong.

23
00:02:43,503 --> 00:02:45,970
Such a weakling.

24
00:02:47,035 --> 00:02:54,034
When Minjoon and I were at your age,
we could drink gallons of liquor.

25
00:02:54,035 --> 00:02:59,034
You can't succeed
with that mettle.

26
00:02:59,035 --> 00:03:01,937
You need to start over
at the bottom.

27
00:03:03,035 --> 00:03:06,034
With whose permission?

28
00:03:06,035 --> 00:03:09,035
I didn't give birth to him
to see him suffer.

29
00:03:19,169 --> 00:03:21,303
Mr. Taesoo Park,

30
00:03:22,035 --> 00:03:28,136
you will have no choice
but to do this.

31
00:03:30,035 --> 00:03:33,035
Oh, there you are!

32
00:03:33,703 --> 00:03:36,802
Why didn't you answer?
I looked for you.

33
00:03:36,803 --> 00:03:40,370
Hi. I was
going over something.

34
00:03:41,035 --> 00:03:43,035
What are these?

35
00:03:45,035 --> 00:03:51,336
Remember I told you about
the hospital site in Qingdao?

36
00:03:52,570 --> 00:03:55,068
I know you don't want to
put too many irons in the fire...

37
00:03:55,069 --> 00:03:59,802
but Dr. Choi already signed the paper.

38
00:03:59,803 --> 00:04:03,703
So why don't you...

39
00:04:08,970 --> 00:04:09,970
Honey.

40
00:04:10,937 --> 00:04:17,034
I made it clear that Jaejoon is
too soft-hearted to run a hospital.

41
00:04:17,035 --> 00:04:21,235
Spending money on the hospital
will be a waste of money.

42
00:04:21,236 --> 00:04:24,770
Break the contract and just wait.

43
00:04:26,637 --> 00:04:31,969
Are you going to
discriminate your kids like this?

44
00:04:31,970 --> 00:04:32,303
What?

45
00:04:32,304 --> 00:04:37,034
You encouraged and supported Minjoon
when he started business,

46
00:04:37,035 --> 00:04:40,034
but you put Jaejoon down
before he even starts.

47
00:04:40,035 --> 00:04:43,034
Your favoritism
might break his spirit.

48
00:04:43,035 --> 00:04:44,602
Are you serious?

49
00:04:44,603 --> 00:04:46,168
Yes, I am.

50
00:04:46,169 --> 00:04:49,269
Have I ever asked you
a favor for Jaejoon?

51
00:04:49,270 --> 00:04:55,335
I've endured a lot for the peace
in the family but this is too much.

52
00:04:55,336 --> 00:04:59,034
Tell me.
What's so wrong with him?

53
00:04:59,035 --> 00:05:00,035
Well, listen.

54
00:05:00,036 --> 00:05:05,536
He became a doctor because
you wanted to have a doctor son.

55
00:05:05,537 --> 00:05:10,302
He also flew to Taiwan to date a girl
because you told him to.

56
00:05:10,303 --> 00:05:14,602
He does whatever you tell him.
So why do you hate him so much?

57
00:05:14,603 --> 00:05:16,202
That's the problem!

58
00:05:16,203 --> 00:05:21,836
He is a man but he's so sissy
and dependent to his parents!

59
00:05:21,837 --> 00:05:26,402
With that soft mettle,
what can he achieve in this tough world?

60
00:05:26,403 --> 00:05:30,034
Then should he be like
defiant Minjoon...

61
00:05:30,035 --> 00:05:33,034
who started business at will,

62
00:05:33,035 --> 00:05:36,903
who married and divorced
of his own accord?

63
00:05:36,904 --> 00:05:40,034
Wasn't it enough for you
to invest in his business?

64
00:05:40,035 --> 00:05:43,034
Must you always put him
before Jaejoon?

65
00:05:43,035 --> 00:05:45,034
Are you done?

66
00:05:45,035 --> 00:05:48,034
How could you
draw the line between them?

67
00:05:48,035 --> 00:05:50,636
Both Minjoon and Jaejoon
are precious to me.

68
00:05:50,637 --> 00:05:54,836
Every child is dear to his parents!

69
00:05:54,837 --> 00:05:58,034
You are really disappointing me!

70
00:05:58,035 --> 00:06:01,235
Disappointing?
YOU are disappointing.

71
00:06:01,236 --> 00:06:08,034
For our 30 years of married life,
how have I treated you and Minjoon?

72
00:06:08,035 --> 00:06:11,034
He still doesn't
regard me as his mother...

73
00:06:11,035 --> 00:06:14,034
and keeps his distance from me.

74
00:06:14,035 --> 00:06:19,135
But I've always smiled at him
and put him before my own son!

75
00:06:19,136 --> 00:06:21,034
Honey, listen.

76
00:06:21,035 --> 00:06:24,302
Don't tell me to let it pass.

77
00:06:24,303 --> 00:06:29,034
If you really
regard them equally,

78
00:06:29,035 --> 00:06:32,769
prove it to me
before you support Minjoon.

79
00:06:32,770 --> 00:06:38,269
Otherwise, I will never believe you!
Do you understand?

80
00:06:38,270 --> 00:06:39,270
Honey.

81
00:06:45,035 --> 00:06:47,035
- Heera.
- Heera.

82
00:06:47,637 --> 00:06:52,936
My daughter, Heera.
What's the matter?

83
00:06:52,937 --> 00:06:55,034
Where are you
going to go at this hour?

84
00:06:55,035 --> 00:06:57,270
Right, it's late at night.

85
00:06:58,035 --> 00:07:00,034
You really want to
take it this far?

86
00:07:00,035 --> 00:07:04,602
Don't raise your voice!
It's your fault!

87
00:07:04,603 --> 00:07:10,269
You should humbly beg for
her forgiveness instead of yelling at her.

88
00:07:10,270 --> 00:07:13,335
Stop her.
Oh, Heera! Heera!

89
00:07:13,336 --> 00:07:18,034
Let her go!
She is not in her right mind.

90
00:07:18,035 --> 00:07:23,904
Do as you like!
Let's have it our ways!

91
00:07:27,937 --> 00:07:30,035
How cold-hearted!

92
00:07:31,035 --> 00:07:34,602
I cast pearl before swine.

93
00:07:34,603 --> 00:07:40,035
Can't believe I gave
my daughter to him. You're a devil!

94
00:07:44,035 --> 00:07:46,236
Margherita is ready!

95
00:07:52,035 --> 00:07:53,369
Taste it.

96
00:07:53,370 --> 00:07:57,370
Margherita will add
rich flavor to this.

97
00:08:01,703 --> 00:08:06,035
Let's taste the upgraded taste
of our top-selling pizza.

98
00:08:15,035 --> 00:08:17,736
The cheese tastes really good
with spicy chicken.

99
00:08:17,737 --> 00:08:18,737
Yes.

100
00:08:19,803 --> 00:08:21,168
This is the very taste.

101
00:08:21,169 --> 00:08:24,136
I'm sure it'll
receive a great response.

102
00:08:28,035 --> 00:08:30,035
Oh, yes.

103
00:08:30,570 --> 00:08:32,970
It'll go very well
with a drink, too.

104
00:08:37,035 --> 00:08:38,670
It's good.

105
00:08:39,035 --> 00:08:43,036
We can do more sales in the evening
if we release this.

106
00:08:44,036 --> 00:08:45,036
Wait.

107
00:08:46,035 --> 00:08:49,069
How about moving up
the release date?

108
00:08:56,069 --> 00:08:59,034
Meeting on 15th...

109
00:08:59,035 --> 00:09:01,703
Oh, we're on a tight schedule.

110
00:09:02,803 --> 00:09:04,536
Can I ask you a quiz?

111
00:09:04,537 --> 00:09:05,537
Quiz?

112
00:09:06,035 --> 00:09:10,802
Guess you're poor at Korean history
since you lived abroad.

113
00:09:10,803 --> 00:09:14,602
What are you talking about?
I lived in Korea until I turned 20.

114
00:09:14,603 --> 00:09:16,603
Then you can guess the answer.

115
00:09:17,203 --> 00:09:23,034
Of all kings in Korean history,
guess who held the lowest position.

116
00:09:23,035 --> 00:09:25,737
The lowest position?

117
00:09:26,904 --> 00:09:28,035
Let me think.

118
00:09:29,069 --> 00:09:30,970
Yeonsangoon?

119
00:09:31,169 --> 00:09:33,636
Kwanghaegoon?
Uijawang?

120
00:09:33,637 --> 00:09:34,637
Beep!

121
00:09:35,203 --> 00:09:36,636
Your guesses are wrong.

122
00:09:36,637 --> 00:09:38,035
The answer is...

123
00:09:39,270 --> 00:09:41,270
the minimum wage.

124
00:09:45,035 --> 00:09:46,770
Sorry for the lame joke.

125
00:09:48,035 --> 00:09:52,004
I think you need
a little balance.

126
00:09:54,570 --> 00:09:56,937
I look like a workaholic, huh?

127
00:09:57,503 --> 00:10:02,034
But I really feel rushed.

128
00:10:02,035 --> 00:10:07,034
I worked frantically hard
to achieve something in life.

129
00:10:07,035 --> 00:10:11,737
But I always ended up
empty-handed.

130
00:10:11,770 --> 00:10:17,470
If I fail this time,
my life will end up in failure.

131
00:10:18,670 --> 00:10:23,603
I push ahead hard
not to miss the chance.

132
00:10:26,403 --> 00:10:29,769
I know how you think of me.

133
00:10:29,770 --> 00:10:34,035
I'm frantic and
reckless to your eyes.

134
00:10:35,670 --> 00:10:43,670
That's fine.
Just understand that I have a reason.

135
00:10:49,537 --> 00:10:51,270
My service to you.

136
00:11:04,603 --> 00:11:10,034
I'm so bitter and resentful!

137
00:11:10,035 --> 00:11:14,034
This is ridiculous!

138
00:11:14,035 --> 00:11:20,034
How dare he preach
a homily to my daughter!

139
00:11:20,035 --> 00:11:26,034
He's completely uneducated but
she is an Ewha grad.

140
00:11:26,035 --> 00:11:30,034
It's him who should
listen to her!

141
00:11:30,035 --> 00:11:34,034
I don't think so.
Taesoo is right.

142
00:11:34,035 --> 00:11:38,103
It's true Jaejoon is a bit too
weak-hearted, isn't it?

143
00:11:40,737 --> 00:11:42,569
How can you say that?

144
00:11:42,570 --> 00:11:48,135
When we should close ranks
and attack Taesoo, you're saying what?

145
00:11:48,136 --> 00:11:51,637
Cut the crap and just pack up!

146
00:11:55,470 --> 00:11:57,303
<Husband>

147
00:12:02,670 --> 00:12:07,436
The person you have dialed
is not available.

148
00:12:08,503 --> 00:12:13,034
Dang it.
Where on earth did she go?

149
00:12:13,035 --> 00:12:15,035
I'm so resentful!

150
00:12:15,503 --> 00:12:18,034
Changsoo, get the car ready!

151
00:12:18,035 --> 00:12:19,870
Okay.

152
00:12:20,870 --> 00:12:22,469
Where are you going
this late at night?

153
00:12:22,470 --> 00:12:24,702
You really don't know?

154
00:12:24,703 --> 00:12:30,102
Hope you enjoy your
solitary life in this big house.

155
00:12:30,103 --> 00:12:33,034
I will go to my daughter...

156
00:12:33,035 --> 00:12:37,034
and make a living by ourselves.

157
00:12:37,035 --> 00:12:39,669
We are history now.

158
00:12:39,670 --> 00:12:41,035
Wait!

159
00:12:46,035 --> 00:12:49,035
Are you adding oil to the fire?

160
00:12:49,837 --> 00:12:50,969
What?

161
00:12:50,970 --> 00:12:55,802
Okay, leave.
But keep this in mind.

162
00:12:55,803 --> 00:12:59,135
You are free to go but
you can't come back at your will.

163
00:12:59,136 --> 00:13:02,302
What?
Is that a threat?

164
00:13:02,303 --> 00:13:05,335
Yes, it's a threat.
Go ahead, leave.

165
00:13:05,336 --> 00:13:06,435
Leave my house.

166
00:13:06,436 --> 00:13:10,837
What?
You think I'm afraid?

167
00:13:16,035 --> 00:13:21,035
What's wrong with this?
Is it broken?

168
00:13:23,403 --> 00:13:25,569
It won't move.

169
00:13:25,570 --> 00:13:29,034
Changsoo, I think the
wheels are broken.

170
00:13:29,035 --> 00:13:30,636
Let's go back in.

171
00:13:30,637 --> 00:13:32,035
They're turning well.

172
00:13:32,537 --> 00:13:34,136
Listen, Taesoo.

173
00:13:35,136 --> 00:13:40,034
I'm going back to my room
when you told me to leave,

174
00:13:40,035 --> 00:13:43,335
but don't think
I got scared by your threat.

175
00:13:43,336 --> 00:13:47,936
Once I fix the wheels,
I'll leave right away. Changsoo.

176
00:13:47,937 --> 00:13:50,936
Go get a screwdriver
and come in with this.

177
00:13:50,937 --> 00:13:52,034
The wheels are fine.

178
00:13:52,035 --> 00:13:53,302
Just shut up and come in!

179
00:13:53,303 --> 00:13:56,035
We can leave. Mom!

180
00:14:02,036 --> 00:14:05,034
By the way,
where on earth has she gone?

181
00:14:05,035 --> 00:14:07,035
It's dangerous at night.

182
00:14:18,035 --> 00:14:25,303
Well, I've endured for 30 years.
I can't give up now.

183
00:14:36,570 --> 00:14:42,436
I will roust Minjoon and
let Jaejoon have the hospital.

184
00:15:03,303 --> 00:15:08,034
I worked frantically hard
to achieve something in life.

185
00:15:08,035 --> 00:15:11,537
But I always
ended up empty-handed.

186
00:15:27,670 --> 00:15:29,570
I dozed off again.

187
00:15:30,670 --> 00:15:35,035
I always put my
worst foot forward.

188
00:15:37,637 --> 00:15:42,035
Thank you so much
for today. Good night.

189
00:15:49,035 --> 00:15:50,203
Lena.

190
00:15:59,937 --> 00:16:06,035
You said your life might end up
in failure if you fail this time.

191
00:16:08,035 --> 00:16:10,035
That'll never happen.

192
00:16:10,570 --> 00:16:15,035
This time,
you have me by your side.

193
00:16:21,537 --> 00:16:23,136
Thank you.

194
00:16:24,436 --> 00:16:26,035
Drive safely.

195
00:16:55,035 --> 00:16:56,637
What's wrong with me?

196
00:16:59,603 --> 00:17:02,370
Why is my heart racing?

197
00:17:07,035 --> 00:17:09,035
Get a grip.

198
00:17:10,035 --> 00:17:12,336
You still didn't learn a lesson?

199
00:17:13,737 --> 00:17:17,336
Men eat the orange
and throw the peel away.

200
00:17:18,737 --> 00:17:24,203
He's only a ladder
for my success.

201
00:18:07,035 --> 00:18:09,034
Is it your marriage ring?

202
00:18:09,035 --> 00:18:13,035
I read an article
about your love for your wife.

203
00:18:35,470 --> 00:18:37,136
Excuse us.

204
00:18:39,035 --> 00:18:40,769
We came to see
if we can work here.

205
00:18:40,770 --> 00:18:43,035
I don't hire inexperienced people.

206
00:18:43,036 --> 00:18:45,235
I'm not inexperienced.

207
00:18:45,236 --> 00:18:49,769
I made stuffed animals
in Taiwan for 3 years.

208
00:18:49,770 --> 00:18:56,136
And I picked bananas
and pineapples there for 4 years.

209
00:18:57,035 --> 00:18:58,169
Really?

210
00:18:58,203 --> 00:19:02,202
So you have
international experience.

211
00:19:02,203 --> 00:19:07,034
Yes. If you give us a chance,
we'll do anything.

212
00:19:07,035 --> 00:19:09,269
Come on,
don't say like an amateur.

213
00:19:09,270 --> 00:19:13,502
Everybody in this
Whiz Sideline is a pro.

214
00:19:13,503 --> 00:19:15,103
Take a look around.

215
00:19:29,570 --> 00:19:32,236
They seem to be whizzes.

216
00:19:33,035 --> 00:19:36,035
Can we do it like they do?

217
00:20:08,035 --> 00:20:10,035
Enough.
You may leave.

218
00:20:10,737 --> 00:20:12,270
Bastard.

219
00:20:14,136 --> 00:20:16,303
I wonder if he is alright.

220
00:20:19,503 --> 00:20:21,336
I almost scorched it!

221
00:20:23,603 --> 00:20:26,035
It's done.

222
00:20:29,004 --> 00:20:31,035
Where's my recipe notebook?

223
00:20:35,970 --> 00:20:38,702
Esol, hurry.
You might be late for job interviews.

224
00:20:38,703 --> 00:20:41,369
Can't you knock?
You scared me.

225
00:20:41,370 --> 00:20:47,034
Oh, sorry.
Hurry up. I'll go out.

226
00:20:47,035 --> 00:20:50,202
Wait. Have you seen
my recipe notebook?

227
00:20:50,203 --> 00:20:52,035
I can't find it anywhere.

228
00:20:58,004 --> 00:20:59,004
Hey.

229
00:21:00,035 --> 00:21:01,102
Don't you think
you're going too far?

230
00:21:01,103 --> 00:21:05,502
Why?
Oh, because I lost it?

231
00:21:05,503 --> 00:21:09,068
No, it's not that.
I'm a man.

232
00:21:09,069 --> 00:21:15,203
How can you crawl around
in your underwear in my presence?

233
00:21:16,036 --> 00:21:18,802
You're not a man to me.

234
00:21:18,803 --> 00:21:22,202
We used to swim in our skin
and go to a bathhouse when little.

235
00:21:22,203 --> 00:21:23,203
Hey!

236
00:21:24,870 --> 00:21:27,034
I'm not who I used to be.

237
00:21:27,035 --> 00:21:30,937
I'm a grown up, mature man!

238
00:21:34,904 --> 00:21:37,034
What's wrong with him?

239
00:21:37,035 --> 00:21:39,169
Is he at the awkward age?

240
00:21:40,035 --> 00:21:43,035
By the way,
where on earth has it gone?

241
00:21:58,537 --> 00:22:03,168
Jaejoon, give me 30,
or at least 10 minutes.

242
00:22:03,169 --> 00:22:09,035
I need to explain
what happened. Please.

243
00:22:12,035 --> 00:22:13,136
Jaejoon,

244
00:22:14,035 --> 00:22:18,003
your mom and dad had a
big fight last night over your hospital.

245
00:22:18,004 --> 00:22:22,034
I spoke with Mom.
She needs some time alone.

246
00:22:22,035 --> 00:22:23,035
Huh?

247
00:22:23,036 --> 00:22:27,202
Why don't you act charming
and pester your dad?

248
00:22:27,203 --> 00:22:31,536
"Dad, can you set up
a hospital for me? Please." Like this.

249
00:22:31,537 --> 00:22:33,034
- Uncle Changsoo.
- Yes?

250
00:22:33,035 --> 00:22:38,035
Don't worry.
They'll stop fighting over that matter.

251
00:22:40,436 --> 00:22:42,169
What does he mean?

252
00:22:44,035 --> 00:22:46,035
There's a bite in his words.

253
00:22:51,035 --> 00:22:53,035
Why is it still on YouTube?

254
00:22:53,470 --> 00:22:56,203
Didn't you ask the police
to delete video clips?

255
00:22:57,035 --> 00:22:58,068
I did.

256
00:22:58,069 --> 00:23:02,269
Then why are some
still on the Internet?

257
00:23:02,270 --> 00:23:05,034
They keep spreading them.

258
00:23:05,035 --> 00:23:11,436
Yura became famous overnight,
"Water Bombed Club Girl!"

259
00:23:12,503 --> 00:23:17,903
Be quiet.
Did you tie Jaejoon's tongue?

260
00:23:17,904 --> 00:23:19,034
Who knows?

261
00:23:19,035 --> 00:23:23,035
Yura constantly called him
but he didn't answer.

262
00:23:24,904 --> 00:23:26,870
I'm going nuts.

263
00:23:30,737 --> 00:23:31,737
No.

264
00:23:32,303 --> 00:23:35,035
I'm not Hyejin
if I back off here.

265
00:23:36,035 --> 00:23:40,034
Heera is quiet, which means
she doesn't know about it yet.

266
00:23:40,035 --> 00:23:42,502
I must persuade Jaejoon
once he comes to work.

267
00:23:42,503 --> 00:23:45,603
Will he come to work?

268
00:23:46,436 --> 00:23:48,034
He saw everything?

269
00:23:48,035 --> 00:23:51,034
Shut the mouth.

270
00:23:51,035 --> 00:23:54,034
But from a
common-sense point of view...

271
00:23:54,035 --> 00:23:55,637
One, two!

272
00:24:02,370 --> 00:24:05,769
Yes. Did Dr. Park
come to work?

273
00:24:05,770 --> 00:24:08,035
Yes, he just went up.

274
00:24:13,103 --> 00:24:16,370
Okay. The game is on.

275
00:24:19,035 --> 00:24:20,737
Jaejoon.

276
00:24:23,004 --> 00:24:26,004
I have to work.
Please get out.

277
00:24:27,035 --> 00:24:31,235
No. I came since you
didn't answer the phone.

278
00:24:31,236 --> 00:24:36,034
I know you're upset
but please listen to me.

279
00:24:36,035 --> 00:24:39,869
I'm not upset.
I'll tell Dr. Choi everything.

280
00:24:39,870 --> 00:24:42,969
Like what?
You mean you'll break up with me?

281
00:24:42,970 --> 00:24:44,035
Yura.

282
00:24:44,270 --> 00:24:47,770
No! Please don't do that.

283
00:24:48,436 --> 00:24:50,936
Don't be so petty.

284
00:24:50,937 --> 00:24:55,102
Girls at my age go out
on the razzle at a club.

285
00:24:55,103 --> 00:24:59,034
I learned all sorts of dances
since I was little.

286
00:24:59,035 --> 00:25:01,670
Korean dance,
ballet, jazz dance...

287
00:25:02,136 --> 00:25:07,537
So when I hear music,
my body moves in spite of myself.

288
00:25:08,470 --> 00:25:10,035
I have to work.

289
00:25:11,303 --> 00:25:13,035
No. You can't go!

290
00:25:13,637 --> 00:25:16,636
You can't move an inch
before you change your mind.

291
00:25:16,637 --> 00:25:18,035
Yura.

292
00:25:18,436 --> 00:25:21,502
Jaejoon, cut me some slack.

293
00:25:21,503 --> 00:25:27,034
I will quit drinking and clubbing
if you tell me not to.

294
00:25:27,035 --> 00:25:34,035
If you break up with me,
I'll be dead in my mom's hands.

295
00:25:36,035 --> 00:25:38,035
Do you love me?

296
00:25:39,203 --> 00:25:40,136
I'm sorry?

297
00:25:40,137 --> 00:25:42,570
Do you love me enough
to marry me?

298
00:25:44,970 --> 00:25:46,303
Well...

299
00:25:49,035 --> 00:25:52,937
I'm not mad at you.

300
00:25:53,436 --> 00:25:55,770
On the contrary, I thank you.

301
00:25:57,035 --> 00:26:00,402
We both were
pushed to marry but...

302
00:26:00,403 --> 00:26:04,034
you being honest with yourself
encouraged me.

303
00:26:04,035 --> 00:26:07,034
Let's break up for both of us.

304
00:26:07,035 --> 00:26:08,035
Jaejoon.

305
00:26:08,036 --> 00:26:12,236
Don't worry.
I won't cause you damage.

306
00:26:13,035 --> 00:26:16,034
Jaejoon, wait.

307
00:26:16,035 --> 00:26:19,436
Break up?
With whose permission?

308
00:26:21,035 --> 00:26:23,103
You think it's possible?

309
00:26:24,035 --> 00:26:26,669
Didn't you hear what she said?

310
00:26:26,670 --> 00:26:29,335
She only danced at a club.

311
00:26:29,336 --> 00:26:32,736
She was highlighted
since she was outstanding.

312
00:26:32,737 --> 00:26:37,669
She didn't have a fling with a man
or have a dirty past.

313
00:26:37,670 --> 00:26:42,035
Her dance at the club
can't be a ground for breakup.

314
00:26:43,035 --> 00:26:44,035
Right.

315
00:26:44,036 --> 00:26:49,035
You're mutually at fault.
You too had fun at the club.

316
00:26:54,035 --> 00:26:56,870
Please accept my resignation.

317
00:26:59,035 --> 00:27:02,870
Were you this foolish?

318
00:27:03,770 --> 00:27:07,034
Can't you see what
your breakup means?

319
00:27:07,035 --> 00:27:13,034
Your marriage is not just
about you and Yura...

320
00:27:13,035 --> 00:27:17,737
but more about business
beyond the two families.

321
00:27:18,303 --> 00:27:22,034
Yet, will you break up with her
and neuter the great synergy...

322
00:27:22,035 --> 00:27:28,135
from your marriage just because
you think she's ill-behaved?

323
00:27:28,136 --> 00:27:31,769
Yes, I will break up with her.

324
00:27:31,770 --> 00:27:37,035
I'd rather listen to my heart than hope
to get a rake-off from the synergy.

325
00:27:37,036 --> 00:27:40,034
What? Dr. Park!

326
00:27:40,035 --> 00:27:43,034
I don't want to ruin
your friendship with my mother.

327
00:27:43,035 --> 00:27:45,669
I'll bear all the responsibility.

328
00:27:45,670 --> 00:27:49,336
Thank you for everything.

329
00:27:57,035 --> 00:28:00,034
Boy. He's manly.

330
00:28:00,035 --> 00:28:01,035
What?

331
00:28:01,036 --> 00:28:04,034
Well, you want me
to bring him back?

332
00:28:04,035 --> 00:28:05,035
One, two, three!

333
00:28:05,036 --> 00:28:08,670
Don't. It won't work.

334
00:28:09,035 --> 00:28:10,770
What's in your mind?

335
00:28:11,035 --> 00:28:12,035
Can I break up with him?

336
00:28:12,036 --> 00:28:13,270
Are you crazy?

337
00:28:15,035 --> 00:28:19,737
Now I have no choice
but to use the last card.

338
00:28:20,303 --> 00:28:23,035
The last card?
Like what?

339
00:28:23,970 --> 00:28:25,870
You don't need to know.

340
00:28:29,136 --> 00:28:33,135
So you lived in Taiwan.

341
00:28:33,136 --> 00:28:35,435
Yes, I lived there for 6 years.

342
00:28:35,436 --> 00:28:39,369
I got certificates for
Chinese and Korean cuisines there.

343
00:28:39,370 --> 00:28:44,003
Really.
Seems you're industrious.

344
00:28:44,004 --> 00:28:46,034
Why didn't you
go to college then?

345
00:28:46,035 --> 00:28:47,035
Excuse me?

346
00:28:48,035 --> 00:28:53,034
I dropped out of college
for family reasons.

347
00:28:53,035 --> 00:28:57,034
I think field experience is as important
as the school education.

348
00:28:57,035 --> 00:29:02,034
I learned a lot from experience.

349
00:29:02,035 --> 00:29:06,034
Her mother is half-educated.
You can tell her backgrounds.

350
00:29:06,035 --> 00:29:07,035
Really?

351
