Well, you're dressed up today.

352
00:29:14,503 --> 00:29:16,502
Can you dance before us?

353
00:29:16,503 --> 00:29:20,034
Yes. It's written here your hobby
is singing and dancing.

354
00:29:20,035 --> 00:29:21,904
Show us.

355
00:29:24,503 --> 00:29:25,503
Come on.

356
00:29:26,035 --> 00:29:30,034
A good staff these days
can liven up the mood.

357
00:29:30,035 --> 00:29:34,034
Do you know
'Poison' by J.H. Uhm?

358
00:29:34,035 --> 00:29:35,637
Poison.

359
00:29:38,035 --> 00:29:40,803
Yes. I'll do my best.

360
00:30:01,737 --> 00:30:03,069
Keep going.

361
00:30:06,035 --> 00:30:10,035
You're making a fool out of me.

362
00:30:11,035 --> 00:30:15,034
I really need a job
so I came here in desperation.

363
00:30:15,035 --> 00:30:18,770
Even though you're interviewers,
how could you...

364
00:30:20,770 --> 00:30:24,035
You know what?

365
00:30:25,035 --> 00:30:28,035
You can't have the
upper hand over me forever.

366
00:30:29,035 --> 00:30:36,336
I might be back
as your customer someday.

367
00:31:29,203 --> 00:31:33,503
The person you have dialed
is not available.

368
00:31:39,035 --> 00:31:41,402
Mom, I have
something to tell you.

369
00:31:41,403 --> 00:31:43,136
Give me a call
when you get this message.

370
00:32:04,035 --> 00:32:06,035
Chef Esol Kang?

371
00:32:06,503 --> 00:32:08,035
Esol Kang...

372
00:32:10,035 --> 00:32:11,737
Esol Kang?

373
00:32:13,004 --> 00:32:16,035
So you are Esol Kang.

374
00:32:16,837 --> 00:32:21,035
Now I learned your real name.

375
00:32:37,103 --> 00:32:41,034
Monthly Plan of Esol Kang.
Go, Esol! You can do it!

376
00:32:41,035 --> 00:32:47,502
There are so many things I want to do
but I can't because of my family.

377
00:32:47,503 --> 00:32:51,034
Do you have to do this job?

378
00:32:51,035 --> 00:32:55,536
Doesn't it hurt your pride
to sing before drunken men?

379
00:32:55,537 --> 00:33:00,436
Sometimes, there are things
to come before my pride.

380
00:33:30,035 --> 00:33:32,203
It's good!

381
00:33:32,970 --> 00:33:35,135
Paprika tastes
different per color.

382
00:33:35,136 --> 00:33:37,034
Mom, try it.

383
00:33:37,035 --> 00:33:39,869
Paprika is good for your stress.

384
00:33:39,870 --> 00:33:43,034
How indifferent!

385
00:33:43,035 --> 00:33:50,034
How can you possibly eat
when we haven't heard from Heera?

386
00:33:50,035 --> 00:33:54,034
Yes, we have.
She needs some time alone to think.

387
00:33:54,035 --> 00:33:59,737
So what does she
have to think about so long?

388
00:34:00,303 --> 00:34:03,035
Perhaps, something bad
happened to her.

389
00:34:03,904 --> 00:34:08,035
She's pretty, she looks rich.

390
00:34:08,036 --> 00:34:12,034
Someone might have
kidnapped her.

391
00:34:12,035 --> 00:34:13,869
