from the pizza I made.

428
00:36:44,035 --> 00:36:45,202
Yes, it is.

429
00:36:45,203 --> 00:36:48,035
Chicken meat is
as chewy as cheese.

430
00:36:48,036 --> 00:36:50,034
Did you use different chicken?

431
00:36:50,035 --> 00:36:51,035
Yes.

432
00:36:51,036 --> 00:36:54,302
The secret of this pizza
lies in the meat.

433
00:36:54,303 --> 00:36:56,202
See?

434
00:36:56,203 --> 00:36:57,703
Shut up.

435
00:36:58,303 --> 00:37:00,103
I know that much.

436
00:37:01,035 --> 00:37:05,034
I think it'll bring us success
with a good marketing.

437
00:37:05,035 --> 00:37:07,435
Thank you for your
hard work so far.

438
00:37:07,436 --> 00:37:09,035
Thank you!

439
00:37:14,004 --> 00:37:16,637
Guess the response was good.

440
00:37:17,035 --> 00:37:18,869
Why yes.

441
00:37:18,870 --> 00:37:23,736
I beat the bush and
Ms. Jeong caught the birds.

442
00:37:23,737 --> 00:37:25,870
This new menu
will be successful.

443
00:37:26,537 --> 00:37:28,035
Good job, everyone.

444
00:37:28,537 --> 00:37:31,034
Ms. Jeong,
you need to come with me.

445
00:37:31,035 --> 00:37:33,537
Sorry? To where?

446
00:37:37,336 --> 00:37:38,769
What the.

447
00:37:38,770 --> 00:37:41,035
They always go in couples.

448
00:37:42,035 --> 00:37:44,270
Are they
seeing each other or what?

449
00:37:49,737 --> 00:37:51,034
What is it?

450
00:37:51,035 --> 00:37:52,969
Mrs. Park,
we got a problem.

451
00:37:52,970 --> 00:37:56,034
Lena Jeong twists
Mr. Park around her finger.

452
00:37:56,035 --> 00:37:58,034
